&lt;h2 id="alert">Alert &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#alert" aria-hidden="true">#&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>&lt;code>alert&lt;/code> outputs its contents as a stylised message box within your article. It&amp;rsquo;s useful for drawing attention to important information that you don&amp;rsquo;t want the reader to miss.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The input is written in Markdown so you can format it however you please.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Example:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-md" data-lang="md">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">{{&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span> &lt;span class="nt">alert&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>}}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="gs">**Warning!**&lt;/span> This action is destructive!
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">{{&lt;span class="p">&amp;lt;&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">/&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">alert&lt;/span> &lt;span class="p">&amp;gt;&lt;/span>}}
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;div class="flex rounded-md bg-yellow-100 px-4 py-3 dark:bg-yellow-900">
